            <p>A few weeks ago, I argued that <a href="https://open.substack.com/pub/igors/p/strategy-as-protocol">strategy should become a protocol</a> — explicit, readable by humans, executable by machines. That essay explored what happens when you make strategic logic transparent. This one asks the question it left open: if AI handles the execution, what does the human actually do?</p>
